   100	- new DataField<T>(string name, bool? nullable = null)
   101	- new DataColumn(DataField field, Array data)
   102	- new DataColumn(DataField field, Array definedData, int[] definitionLevels, int[] repetitionLevels)
   103	- await ParquetWriter.CreateAsync(schema, stream)  -> ParquetWriter
   104	    .CompressionMethod = CompressionMethod.Zstd;  .CustomMetadata = IReadOnlyDictionary<string,string>;
   105	    .CreateRowGroup() -> ParquetRowGroupWriter;   rg.WriteColumnAsync(DataColumn)
   106	
   107	Parquet.Net path semantics (DO NOT string-split with '/'):
   108	- A DataField's identity is the leaf object returned by schema.GetDataFields(). Pair each returned
   109	  DataField with the caller-supplied array directly; never parse Path.ToString() with '/'.
   110	- DataField.Path is a FieldPath whose ToString() is DOT-separated (e.g. "spectrum.mz_range.lo"),
   111	  NOT '/'-separated. If a string key is ever needed, use the dot-separated FieldPath, but the write
   112	  helper keys on the DataField objects themselves.
   113	- DataColumn default codec is Snappy; ZSTD MUST be set explicitly on the writer and proven on read.
   114	
   115	Existing ctor analogs (all delegate to base, one arg):
   116	- ParquetSpectrumWriter(ParseInput) : base(parseInput)  // Writer/ParquetSpectrumWriter.cs:43
   117	</interfaces>
   118	</context>
   119	
   120	<constraints>
   121	- Parquet.Net LOW-LEVEL API only (ParquetSchema/DataColumn/ParquetWriter). NEVER ParquetSerializer.
   122	- m/z = float64, intensity = float32 (canonical widths).
   123	- ZIP = STORED (CompressionLevel.NoCompression). Parquet-internal codec = ZSTD (must be set; Parquet.Net
   124	  default is Snappy).
   125	- Plain string / list (32-bit offset) are accepted by the reader; do NOT chase large_string/large_list.
   126	- Build each Parquet facet fully in a MemoryStream (Parquet.Net needs a seekable stream + footer on dispose),
   127	  then write finished bytes into the STORED zip entry. Never hand Parquet.Net a non-seekable zip-entry stream.
   128	- Reuse inherited SpectrumWriter data access (ReadMZData, RetentionTimeFromScanNumber, MSOrder).
   129	  Do NOT re-decode Thermo data.
   130	- Code must be compact. ImplicitUsings is disabled — every `using` must be explicit. Keep files BOM-free.
   131	- NO comments referencing the harness, GSD, process, phases, or spikes anywhere in code.
   132	</constraints>
