   181	  <behavior>
   182	    - Round-trip test: build a schema with a nested struct (mz_range{lo,hi}), a list-of-struct
   183	      (parameters[{name,val?}] with an empty list row and an inner-null val), and two PARALLEL nullable
   184	      top-level structs (spectrum, scan) where each of 3 rows populates exactly one. Write to a MemoryStream
   185	      via the helper, then read back with ParquetReader and assert: spectrum present on rows 0/2 and null on
   186	      row 1; scan present only on row 1; parameters[0] has 2 items with second val null; row 2 list empty.
   187	    - Def/rep-level lock: assert the exact definition/repetition level arrays produced by the `Column`
   188	      helper for the list-of-struct leaf and a parallel-null leaf match the RESEARCH cheat sheet
   189	      (e.g. parameters/item/name -> def {5,5,0,2}, rep {0,1,0,0}; spectrum/index -> def {1,0,1}, rep null).
   190	    - CV-column-name helper: `MS_1000511_ms_level` from (acc "MS:1000511", label "ms_level");
   191	      `MS_1000016_scan_start_time_unit_UO_0000031` when a unit accession is supplied.
   192	    - PARAM field builder returns a StructField with leaf order exactly
   193	      value/integer, value/float, value/string, value/boolean, accession, name, unit.
   194	    - PARAM round-trip with nullables: a row whose Accession, Unit, and String are all null reads back
   195	      as null on those three leaves while the populated row reads back its values.
   196	    - Written file reports ZSTD compression on read-back (PQ-02 internal-codec assertion).
   197	  </behavior>
   198	  <action>
   199	    Create `Writer/MzPeak/MzPeakParquet.cs` (namespace `ThermoRawFileParser.Writer`, BOM-free, explicit
   200	    usings) as a `public static class MzPeakParquet` plus a `public struct MzPeakParam` (public fields:
   201	    long? Integer, double? Float, string String, bool? Boolean, string Accession, string Name, string Unit).
   202	    Accession, Unit, and String are NULLABLE per the PARAM schema; the value-struct column-writer must
   203	    emit null for them via definition levels when absent. (The csproj does not enable nullable reference
   204	    types, so `string` is already nullable — do not write `string?`, which would warn under CS8632.)
   205	    Implement, mirroring the verified pattern in RESEARCH:
   206	    - `public static StructField BuildParamField(string name)` -> the PARAM struct in the documented leaf
   207	      order (value/integer, value/float, value/string, value/boolean, accession, name, unit).
   208	    - `public static string CvColumn(string accession, string label, string unitAccession = null)` ->
   209	      convention `MS_<acc>_<label>[_unit_<NS>_<acc>]` with the `:` in CURIEs replaced by `_`
   210	      (e.g. MS:1000511 -> MS_1000511). CONTRACT: callers pass `label` already normalized to snake_case;
   211	      `CvColumn` performs NO normalization of the label (document this on the method). It only rewrites
   212	      the `:` in accessions.
   213	    - `public static DataColumn Column(DataField field, Array defined, int[] defLevels, int[] repLevels)`
   214	      -> the single named constructor for every column the writer emits. This hides the
   215	      DataColumn(field, definedData, definitionLevels, repetitionLevels) arg order behind one helper so
   216	      def/rep semantics are defined in exactly one place; the round-trip test locks its behavior.
