   296	The csproj targets `net8.0`; this machine has the .NET 10 SDK (10.0.301) and the 9.0/10.0 runtimes but
   297	NOT the .NET 8 runtime. Resolve as follows:
   298	
   299	1. BUILD relies on NuGet auto-restore of the net8 reference/targeting pack
   300	   (`Microsoft.NETCore.App.Ref` 8.x), which the .NET 10 SDK pulls from NuGet automatically. Run a plain
   301	   `dotnet build -c Release ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParser.csproj` first.
   302	2. ONLY IF that restore/build fails with a missing net8 ref pack, install the .NET 8 SDK (which carries
   303	   the ref pack), then rebuild. Do not edit the csproj target framework.
   304	3. RUN/TEST (not build) is where roll-forward applies: the produced net8 assembly executes on the net9/10
   305	   runtime via `DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD=LatestMajor` + `DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD_TO_PRERELEASE=1`. These env exports
   306	   are placed directly inside each verify command that runs `dotnet build`/`run`/`test` above; keep them
   307	   there. Parquet.Net 5.0.1's net8.0 lib loads cleanly under net9/10. Document the chosen approach in the
   308	   SUMMARY.
   309	4. Reference Python OPEN gate needs `python3.11` with `pyarrow`, `pandas`, `numpy`, `pynumpress`, `psims`.
   310	   Install the latter two if absent: `python3.11 -m pip install pynumpress psims`. Force `import numpy.typing`
   311	   before `from mzpeak import MzPeakFile` (older numpy build does not auto-load the typing submodule).
