   313	
   314	<threat_model>
   315	## Trust Boundaries
   316	
   317	| Boundary | Description |
   318	|----------|-------------|
   319	| RAW file -> writer | Thermo RAW is parsed by trusted, already-shipping TRFP reader code (reused, not new) |
   320	| writer -> .mzpeak archive | New code constructs Parquet + zip bytes consumed by external readers |
   321	| .mzpeak -> reference reader | OPEN gate runs an external Python process over the produced file |
   322	
   323	## STRIDE Threat Register
   324	
   325	| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
   326	|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
   327	| T-01-01 | Tampering | mzpeak_index.json lists a facet not actually written | mitigate | Emit JSON listing EXACTLY the two facets written; reader fails OPEN otherwise |
   328	| T-01-02 | Denial of Service | Zero-point spectrum -> empty/invalid facet | mitigate | Select the first in-range spectrum with >= 1 real point; if none, throw RawFileParserException and emit no archive (never fabricate a point) |
   329	| T-01-03 | Information Disclosure | Accidental deflate (CompressionLevel default) breaks STORED contract | mitigate | Force `CompressionLevel.NoCompression`; verify `compress_type==0` in the gate |
   330	| T-01-04 | Tampering | Parquet codec silently left at Snappy default, violating PQ-03 | mitigate | Set `CompressionMethod.Zstd`; gate reads both parquet entries' column-chunk metadata and asserts ZSTD |
   331	| T-01-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | accept | No new C# NuGet packages (Parquet.Net/Newtonsoft already deps). Only pip installs are `pynumpress`/`psims` into the local test env, verified on pypi.org during research; not shipped in output |
   332	</threat_model>
   333	
