   363	<risks>
   364	- Build runtime mismatch (net8 target vs net9/10 machine) — build via NuGet net8 ref-pack restore;
   365	  run/test via roll-forward env vars in the verify commands.
   366	- Reader OPEN requires BOTH `(spectrum, data arrays)` and `(spectrum, metadata)` facets with their KV keys
   367	  (`spectrum_count`, `spectrum_data_point_count`, `spectrum_array_index`, and a `spectrum.index` leaf) —
   368	  baked into Task 3; omission causes KeyError/IndexError in the reader.
   369	- Parquet codec default is Snappy — ZSTD must be set AND proven; the gate reads column-chunk metadata.
   370	- Column write order / nullable-array pitfalls in Parquet.Net — mitigated by pairing each leaf from
   371	  `GetDataFields()` with its array by DataField identity and passing defined-only values via the `Column`
   372	  helper with explicit definition levels (Task 2 helper).
   373	- No in-range spectrum with points — Task 3 throws RawFileParserException rather than fabricating.
