HIGH, ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs:40 and ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs:73, the writer opens/creates the `.mzpeak` output before proving that an in-range scan with points exists; the no-matching-scan path then throws while leaving a zero-byte/partial file and an unclosed `StreamWriter`, violating the “emit NO archive” contract. Move `ConfigureWriter(".mzpeak")` until after scan selection and facet byte construction, and wrap the final output write/close in `try/finally` or delete partial files on failure.

MEDIUM, ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakParquetTests.cs:14, the mzPeak tests only exercise the low-level Parquet helper; they do not lock the shipped CLI/writer behavior claimed by the phase: `OutputFormat.MzPeak` dispatch, `.mzpeak` creation, STORED zip entries, index JSON shape, data/metadata facet presence, ZSTD in both facets, or the no-matching-scan branch. Add an integration test analogous to `WriterTests.TestParquetCentroid` that runs `RawFileParser.Parse(... OutputFormat.MzPeak)` on `small.RAW` and asserts the archive structure and Parquet metadata.

LOW, ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeak/MzPeakParquet.cs:59 and ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeak/MzPeakParquet.cs:69, `WriteAsync` awaits without `ConfigureAwait(false)` while the production caller synchronously blocks via `GetAwaiter().GetResult()` at `MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs:169`; the CLI path is unlikely to deadlock, but this helper is intended as shared foundation code. Add `ConfigureAwait(false)` to the awaits or keep the whole path async where possible.

LOW, ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakParquetTests.cs:143 and ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakParquetTests.cs:148, the PARAM round-trip test describes a “fully populated” PARAM and sets multiple value alternatives in the same row, which does not lock the union-as-struct discipline that only one of integer/float/string/boolean should be populated. Rewrite the fixture to assert one populated value leaf per PARAM row and null definition levels for the other value leaves.

